{"cursor":"12260","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\nIn economies in which exchange has progressed beyond barter to money pricing,\nthe money (or nominal) price may diverge from its ideal representation as\nabstract value previously carried by concrete (or real) exchange. Since the\nfunction of money is the representation of such value abstractly, such\ndivergence is, in a market economy, considered undesirable and unstable. Various\nfactors can cause such distortions in pricing.\n","linknr":376,"url":"Real_versus_nominal_value_(economics)","recorded":1362670706,"links":24,"instances":["economics","economics","economics","legal"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Basic financial concepts","Economics terminology","Inflation","Value"],"headings":["As viewed in Economics","Illustration, notation, and generalization","Uses and examples","Interest rates","See also","Notes","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d4/GDP_PPP_Per_Capita_IMF_2008.svg/200px-GDP_PPP_Per_Capita_IMF_2008.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["value","economics"],["good","economics"],["index","economics"],["peppercorn","legal"]],"members":["index","good","value","peppercorn"],"related":["Economics","Value_(economics)","Good_(economics)","Purchasing_power","Inflation","Gross_domestic_product","Arithmetic","Price_index","Time-series","Cross-section_data","Cost-of-living_index","Price_index","National_Income_and_Product_Accounts","Dichotomy","Real_GDP","Gross_domestic_product","Money","Price_index","Consumer_Price_Index","Purchasing_power","Constant_dollars","National_Income_and_Product_Accounts","Numéraire","Adam_Smith","Real_interest_rate","Nominal_interest_rate","Inflation","Constant_Item_Purchasing_Power_Accounting","Aggregation_proble